I have a Betta who was tankmates with several other fish who over
time, have died. I decided to replace them with female Bettas hoping
that would be more fun for all. I kept the females together but
separate for a week while they sorted out who was alpha female then
added them to the main tank. Rocky chased the girls around for the
first few days and nipped them a bit but eventually things settled
down. Now it has been a couple of weeks and Rocky's long beautiful
fins are nearly gone. I have been watching them and I have never seen
a female nip him and he still seems to be the boss of the tank. Could
it just be stress? Or are the girls just waiting until I'm not
looking? I'm not sure what to do.
